SBP of 120 mmHg, total/HDL ratio of 4, and HbA(1c) of 6%.
CONCLUSION: Life expectancy tables provide a potentially useful tool of 
conveying prognostic information to people with type 2 diabetes and suggest 
substantial scope for increasing longevity by improving modifiable risk factors.

